[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = WeaponSystems","category":"page"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for WeaponSystems.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Introduction","page":"Home","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package creates used to describe weapon systems","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using WeaponSystems","category":"page"},{"location":"#Table-of-contents","page":"Home","title":"Table of contents","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Pages = [\"index.md\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Package-Features","page":"Home","title":"Package Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Targets","page":"Home","title":"Targets","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Circular and rectangular target definition","category":"page"},{"location":"#Weapon-systems","page":"Home","title":"Weapon systems","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Tank","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [WeaponSystems]","category":"page"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.Canon","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.Canon","text":"The Canon is defined by:\n* θ elevation angle (degrees)\n* lw the length of the canon\n* u₀ the muzzle velocity magnitude\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.Hull","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.Hull","text":"The Hull is defined by :\n* Φ: angle of rotation of the tank around the longitudinal axis. If the right side of the tank is lower than the left side,\nthan this angle is positif.\n* Ψ: angle defined by the longitudinal axes of the tank and the horizontal plane\nIf the nose of the tank is higher than the back, this angle is positif\n* Χ: angle defined by the the projection of the longitudinal axis of the tank into an horizontal plane\nand the X axis\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.Sight","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.Sight","text":"The sight is defined by:\n* θ LOS elevation angle\n* ξ LOS azimuth angle\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.Tank","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.Tank","text":"The tank is defined by: a hull, a turret, a canon, a sight and its position (altitude)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.TargetCirc","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.TargetCirc","text":"TargetCirc(ρ,position)\n\ndefines a circular target by specifying the radius ρ and the position (range)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.TargetRect","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.TargetRect","text":"TargetRect(a,b,position)\n\ndefines a rectangular target by specifying the lenght a, the height b and the position (range)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.TargetSphe","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.TargetSphe","text":"TargetSphe(ρ,position)\n\ndefines a spherical target by specifying the radius ρ and the position (range)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.Turret","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.Turret","text":"The turret is defined by its azimuth angle\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.muzzlePos-Tuple{Tank}","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.muzzlePos","text":"muzzlePos(tank)\n\nReturns the coordinates of the muzzle exit in a coordinate system which has the origin on the tank at the base of the the canon\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#WeaponSystems.targetPos-Tuple{ExternalBallistics.AbstractTarget, Tank}","page":"Home","title":"WeaponSystems.targetPos","text":"targetPos(target,tank)\n\nIs a function that returns the coordinates of the target in a coordinate system which has the origin on the tank at the base of the the canon\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"}]
